Params: You double-check the address one last time.
Signed with a panda clutching bamboo.
You just know Pulao's cooking up another scheme.
Pulao's voice reverberates through the streets.
Unlike the sprawling art galleries in Constellia, this place is clearly a shopping street akin to Babylonia's commercial district.
Though there are no signs hanging around, spots have been reserved.
Glancing toward Pulao, you see two familiar faces, or rather, three.
Changyu and Sophia are talking with someone.
The Little League is getting down to business, shhh—
Hit a snag with the secret plan?
Judging by the person chatting with Changyu, they seem like an ordinary mechanoid.
They're from a Constellia group called the "World Folklore Enthusiasts".
They want to join our Little League for the Valentine's Day market.
The idea was mine! I've booked a whole commercial street!
But they want to use the square as their event space, which means no stalls for us.
Pulao hogs the whole street by herself, so now we gotta cram in more stalls to make a profit.
Holding the event in the central district would be a huge win for public interest in Kowloong folklore!
And after crunching the numbers, this spot's the sweet spot!
We forked out big money for this place.
Whose side are you even on...
We can only spare one stall for you.
If you need anything else, I can cut you a deal on booth rent.
Damn, do I really have to play hardball?
A club member whips out a deck of cards with Constellia designs and a hefty bag.
This is our tradition, gambling with these cards.
It's all about guessing the next card's value to win or lose—
Feels like deja vu. Didn't we have a similar group around this time last year...
You know us well! Ready for a showdown, huh. So, if I win, we get to host our event here. If I lose, we'll pack up and scram!
It was the Little League's deal; we don't have to take any challenge.
Yeah, like there's even a slim chance of winning.
Pulao opens the heavy bag stuffed with things.
As soon as it's opened, there's a flash of silver, revealing a sack full of special coins.
Cool! Give me that! I'm all in!
The alliance decided to have a vote. I'm not in favor of it.
If we lose, you'll get the coins we minted for the event, "Moonlit Night".
Maybe there's a way to make this a win-win?
Classic 【kuroname】. We could team up, you know.
We'll give you the space, but we'll charge an entry fee. After that, it's a 60-40 split, and we take sixty.
And for the card games, all transactions today are with "Moonlit Coin".
Only winners of the card games can snag those coins, giving us a chance to charge for the game.
Pulao tugs at the hem of your shirt, whispering.
No problem. I'm cool with that!
Plus, with such a big street and not many vendors yet, we can lend a hand too.
But we won't be paying top money for labor.
It's our contribution to cultural research.
Oh, and Commandant, want to be the first to try your hand at this game? You can bring along whoever you fancy too.
Here's the deal: you gotta come up with tons of improvements for us!
